label="Topic" /><category relevance="57" term="Hobbies and Pastimes" label="Topic" /><category relevance="57" term="Video Games" label="Topic" /><content type="xhtml"><div id="1">&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;Platforms: &lt;/B&gt;X360, PS3, PC&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;The Deal:&lt;/B&gt; In his last adventure, Ezio Auditore removed the Templar presence from Rome while leaping and running across the vast, populated landscape. Now three years have passed, and our noble assassin still has many questions that desperately need answering. His newfound quest leads him into the footsteps of Altair ibn La'Ahad, a legendary mentor who has locked a source of great power within his library. Now Ezio must travel to the bustling city of Constantinople and find the five keys that will unlock the library before the Templars can gain access and use the power to achieve their goals of death and destruction.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;quot;Assassin's Creed: Revelations&amp;quot; is a third-person action/adventure title that places you in the nimble shoes of Ezio and Altair as you guide them through the streets of Constantinople. With everyone from Templars to Ottoman Janissaries hunting you down, it will become necessary to employ stealth, speed and keen combat skills to avoid a cruel fate. To gain the upper hand, you'll be given a hookblade, a tool used by the Ottoman assassins that facilitates movement through the city and helps you gain an edge while fighting. If the hookblade isn't enough of an advantage, try your hand at bomb crafting. This handy skill will have you building any number of explosive devices.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;The &amp;quot;Assassin's Creed&amp;quot; franchise offers fun, open-world adventure that brings the player into the story through clever gameplay and visuals. &amp;quot;Revelations&amp;quot; takes that a bit further and offers the same thrilling adventure but with a pile of enhancements that will have fans smiling ear to ear.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/c8FtknPdV-Q" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;</div></content><rights type="text">Copyright (c) dose.ca</rights><source><title type="html">Review: Assassin's Creed: Revelations</title><subtitle type="html">This third-person action/adventure title places you in the nimble shoes of Ezio and Altair.</subtitle><id>tag:www.dose.ca:content=5946755</id><rights type="html">Copyright (c) dose.ca</rights><updated>2012-01-04T22:05:54Z</updated><category term="Assassin's Creed: Revelations" label="ConTopic" /><category term="Tribune Media Services" label="Distributor" /><category term="STRY" label="ContentTypeCode" /><category term="DOSE" label="Catalog" /><category term="Y" label="Comments" /><category term="UTF8" label="Format" /><category relevance="97" term="Istanbul" label="City" /><category relevance="54" term="Rome (Italy)" label="City" /><category relevance="54" term="Europe" label="Continent" /><category relevance="54" term="Italy" label="Country" /><category relevance="54" term="Auditore , Ezio" label="Individual" /><category relevance="100" term="317~Istanbul~Sony PlayStation3~Europe~Ezio Auditore" label="InformQString" /><category relevance="54" term="Ezio Auditore" label="Person" /><category relevance="34" term="Assassin's Creed" label="Product" /><category relevance="37" term="Assassin's Creed: Revelations" label="Product" /><category relevance="62" term="Sony PlayStation3" label="Product" /><category relevance="54" term="Southern Europe" label="Regions" /><category relevance="57" term="Culture and Lifestyle" label="Topic" /><category relevance="57" term="Games" label="Topic" /><category relevance="57" term="Hobbies and Pastimes" label="Topic" /><category relevance="57" term="Video Games" label="Topic" /><generator>(c) Postmedia Network Inc.</generator><link href="http://www.dose.ca/5946755.ATOM" rel="alternate" type="application/atom+xml" title="Review: Assas